---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does it cost to paint a house in Hobart in 2026?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Typical 2026 Hobart bands. Interior repaint: a single room $300–$750, a standard 3-bedroom interior (walls, ceilings, doors, skirting, architraves) $4,500–$9,000 depending on ceiling height and surface condition. Exterior: a single-storey 3-bedroom home $9,000–$16,000, a double-storey or weatherboard home $12,000–$20,000+ once you account for scaffold and the heavy preparation weatherboard needs. Roof painting: metal roof $20–$30/m², tile roof $25–$35/m², most Hobart roofs $2,500–$8,000. On a weatherboard repaint, expect roughly 75–85% of the cost to be preparation, application and clean-up — the paint itself is a small part. Every quote is fixed and itemised after we see the property." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does paint fail faster in Hobart than on the mainland?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Hobart's cold, damp maritime climate is hard on paint. Long cool wet stretches keep timber and render damp, which feeds mould and mildew and lifts coatings off poorly-prepared surfaces. Salt air rolling off the Derwent adds another corrosion load on exterior work and metal roofs. The result is a shorter repaint cycle than the warm dry mainland — most Hobart exteriors need recoating every 7–10 years, sooner on exposed weatherboard. The defence is preparation: thorough wash, mould treatment, sanding, filling, priming bare timber, and using paints rated for cool damp conditions. Cutting prep to save money is the single biggest reason a Hobart paint job fails early." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My home is pre-1970 — do I need to worry about lead paint?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. The vast majority of Australian homes built before 1970 contain lead paint, often at high concentrations, and lead in paint was only limited to 1% by 1970. Plenty of Sandy Bay, Battery Point and New Town homes fall into this bracket. Under AS 4361.2 (the guide to lead-paint management) the safe approach is to assume paint on a pre-1997 home is leaded and handle it accordingly: no dry sanding or dry power-tool stripping that throws lead dust around, proper containment and dust capture, drop sheets, and lead-safe clean-up. We're trained in lead-safe practice and prep heritage and pre-1970 homes the right way so your family and the painters aren't exposed." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do I need council approval to paint a heritage home in Hobart?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends. A like-for-like repaint in existing colours usually doesn't need a permit. But if your property is within a City of Hobart heritage precinct or listed on the Tasmanian Heritage Register, a change of colour or scheme can trigger a planning requirement, and works on a listed place may be referred to the Heritage Council. New Town, Battery Point and parts of Sandy Bay have heritage-sensitive areas. We'll flag whether your job is straightforward or whether you should check with the City of Hobart planning team before we lift a brush — and we paint sympathetically to the period either way." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does a Hobart house paint job take?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "An average interior repaint of a 3-bedroom home runs 3–6 working days. An exterior weatherboard repaint runs 7–12 working days, with a large share of that on preparation — sanding, filling, priming bare timber — before any topcoat goes on. Roof painting is usually 1–3 days. Weather is the variable: we don't apply exterior coatings onto damp surfaces or when rain is coming, so a wet Hobart week can stretch the timeline. We schedule around the forecast and keep you posted, and we don't rush prep to hit a date — a properly prepped job lasts years longer." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="House Painters Hobart | Interior, Exterior & Heritage"
  description="Hobart house painters — interior, exterior, roof, heritage & weatherboard, commercial & strata. Cold-climate prep done right, low-VOC paints, AS/NZS 2311 workmanship. Free quote across Greater Hobart."
  canonical="https://hobarthousepainters.com.au/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

<style>
  /* Image-banner integration (added 2026-06-04) */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.72), rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.52)), url('/images/hero.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .hero h1,
  .hero .hero-sub,
  .hero .hero-eyebrow,
  .hero .hero-trust,
  .hero .accent {
    color: #fff;
  }
  .hero .accent {
    color: #fcd34d;
  }
  .hero .hero-eyebrow {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
  }
  .hero .hero-trust {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.78);
  }

  .image-banner {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 460px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .image-banner img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }
  .image-banner figcaption {
    background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.92);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>


  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Sandy Bay &middot; Glenorchy &middot; Kingston &middot; Moonah &middot; New Town</span>
      <h1>House painters in Hobart &mdash; <span class="accent">interior, exterior &amp; heritage</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Interior repaints, weatherboard and render exteriors, roof coating,
        conservation-sensitive heritage work and commercial &amp; strata painting
        across Greater Hobart. We prep properly for the cold, damp maritime
        climate, use low-VOC paints, and work to AS/NZS 2311. Honest fixed
        quotes &mdash; no surprises.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-trust">
        <div><strong>AS/NZS 2311</strong>Painting of buildings</div>
        <div><strong>AS 4361.2</strong>Lead-safe on pre-1970 homes</div>
        <div><strong>Low-VOC</strong>Healthier interior paints</div>
        <div><strong>Heritage</strong>Weatherboard &amp; Georgian</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">What we do</span>
      <h2>Five painting services.</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">
        From a single feature wall through to a full heritage weatherboard
        exterior, a strata block or a roof recoat. One local team, proper
        preparation, low-VOC paints, and a fixed price you can plan around.
      </p>

      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/interior-painting/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9632;</div>
          <h3>Interior house painting</h3>
          <p>Walls, ceilings, trim and doors. Low-VOC paints, neat cut-ins, full prep and protection of your floors and furniture. Tidy, on-time, low-disruption.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See interior painting &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/exterior-painting/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9633;</div>
          <h3>Exterior house painting</h3>
          <p>Weatherboard, render and brick. Wash, mould treatment, sand, fill, prime and recoat &mdash; built to handle Hobart's cold, damp maritime weather.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See exterior painting &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/roof-painting/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9650;</div>
          <h3>Roof painting &amp; coating</h3>
          <p>Metal and tile roofs cleaned, primed and membrane-coated to restore colour and protect against southern weather and salt air off the Derwent.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See roof painting &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/heritage-painting/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9670;</div>
          <h3>Heritage &amp; weatherboard</h3>
          <p>Conservation-sensitive repaints of Federation and Georgian homes with correct preparation and AS 4361.2 lead-paint management on pre-1970 stock.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See heritage painting &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/commercial-painting/">
          <div class="svc-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9744;</div>
          <h3>Commercial &amp; strata</h3>
          <p>Shopfronts, offices and body-corporate exteriors. Low-disruption scheduling, access management and after-hours work where it keeps you trading.</p>
          <span class="svc-link">See commercial painting &rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <figure class="image-banner">
    <img src="/images/result.jpg" alt="Freshly repainted heritage weatherboard home" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    <figcaption>Prep done properly — 10-year system warranty.</figcaption>
  </figure>


  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why a Hobart specialist</span>
      <h2>Three things a Hobart paint job has to get right.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; max-width: 60rem;">
        <div>
          <h3>Preparation beats everything &mdash; especially here.</h3>
          <p>
            On a Hobart exterior, the topcoat is the easy part. The job that
            lasts is in the preparation: a proper wash to strip dirt and salt,
            mould and mildew treatment, sanding back failed coatings, filling
            and re-puttying, and priming every patch of bare timber before a
            drop of finish goes on. On a weatherboard repaint, the bulk of the
            days on site &mdash; often seven of ten &mdash; are preparation. We
            don&rsquo;t cut that corner, because skipped prep is the number-one
            reason a paint job in this climate peels inside a couple of winters.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>The cold, damp maritime climate is unforgiving.</h3>
          <p>
            Hobart&rsquo;s long cool wet stretches keep timber and render damp,
            which feeds mould and lifts paint, while salt air off the Derwent
            adds a corrosion load most mainland cities never deal with. That
            shortens the repaint cycle &mdash; most Hobart exteriors want a
            recoat every <strong>7&ndash;10 years</strong>, sooner on exposed
            southern and waterfront elevations. We use paints rated for cool,
            damp conditions, never coat onto damp surfaces or ahead of rain, and
            schedule around the forecast so the finish actually cures.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Heritage and weatherboard stock needs the right hands.</h3>
          <p>
            Sandy Bay, Battery Point and New Town are full of Federation,
            Georgian and weatherboard homes &mdash; a lot of it pre-1970 and
            very likely carrying <strong>lead paint</strong>. That changes how
            you prepare: no dry sanding that throws lead dust around, proper
            containment and lead-safe clean-up under AS 4361.2. Heritage colour
            schemes and a change of colour can also touch City of Hobart
            heritage-precinct rules. We prep these homes the safe way and paint
            sympathetically to the period.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Service areas</span>
      <h2>Where we paint.</h2>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width: 42rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        Across Greater Hobart &mdash; the inner suburbs, the northern suburbs,
        Kingborough to the south and the eastern shore. Free, no-obligation
        quotes most weeks.
      </p>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/sandy-bay/">Sandy Bay</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/glenorchy/">Glenorchy</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/kingston/">Kingston</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/moonah/">Moonah</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/new-town/">New Town</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hobart-region/">Greater Hobart</a>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Bellerive</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Battery Point</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lindisfarne</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lenah Valley</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">North Hobart</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">South Hobart</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">West Hobart</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Bellerive</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Howrah</span>
        <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Claremont</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <figure class="image-banner">
    <img src="/images/detail.jpg" alt="Paint roller leaving a smooth even finish on timber" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    <figcaption>Premium acrylic, two coats minimum, low-VOC options.</figcaption>
  </figure>


  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2>From quote to clean finish &mdash; 5 stages.</h2>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Free quote</h3><p>We visit, look at surface condition, access and prep needs, and give you a fixed, itemised quote &mdash; not a vague per-hour guess.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Preparation</h3><p>Wash, mould treatment, scrape and sand failed coatings, fill and putty, prime bare timber and patches. The part that makes it last.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Protection</h3><p>Floors, furniture, fixtures, gardens and paths masked and covered. Lead-safe containment on pre-1970 homes under AS 4361.2.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Painting</h3><p>Quality low-VOC paints applied to AS/NZS 2311 &mdash; correct number of coats, neat cut-ins, even coverage. Never onto damp surfaces.</p></div>
        <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><h3>Clean &amp; check</h3><p>Full clean-up, rubbish removed, and a walk-round with you to sign off every surface before we call it done.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Ready for a fresh coat?</h2>
        <p>Interior, exterior, roof, heritage or commercial. Honest fixed quote, proper prep, tidy finish across Greater Hobart.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Articles &amp; guides for Hobart</h2>
      <p>Practical reading from our jobs in Hobart &mdash; what we charge, what to watch for, when a callout is worth it.</p>
      <ul class="guides-list">
          <li><a href="/exterior-repaint-frequency-hobart/">Exterior repaint frequency in Hobart — by substrate</a></li>
          <li><a href="/heritage-colour-match-hobart/">Heritage colour match in Hobart — planning permit zones</a></li>
          <li><a href="/low-voc-hobart/">Low-VOC interior paint in Hobart — newborn-safe selection</a></li>
          <li><a href="/roof-paint-vs-restoration-hobart/">Roof paint vs roof restoration in Hobart — different jobs</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
